msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:442
msgid "Oversweep"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:444
msgid "The emergency wing-sweep handle is also used to select the oversweep position of the wings. The oversweep is only used while on the ground to reduce the wing span to make it easier to spot the aircraft on the carrier deck. As the wing will sweep over the stabilizers on the tail the horizontal tail authority system is enabled to prevent the wings and stabilizers from damaging each other by restricting movement of the stabilizer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:448
msgid "To set the wings to oversweep the emergency wing-sweep handle should be moved to the 68° position and held in the extended position. This will deflate the wing-seal airbags and activate the horizontal tail authority system, indicated by the **HZ TAIL AUTH** caution light illuminating. When the **HZ TAIL AUTH** caution light goes out and the **OVER** flag on the wing-sweep indicator appears the oversweep interlocks are free and the handle can now be moved to the 75° position and stowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:452
msgid "To move the wings out of oversweep the handle is pulled up and moved forwards of 68°. This will again illuminate the **HZ TAIL AUTH** caution light. When the wings have physically exited the oversweep the caution light and the **OVER** flag will turn off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:455
msgid "As with normal emergency mode operation the handle should now be set to the same position as the spider detent and the **MASTER RESET** button depressed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:461
msgid "The controls for the wing-sweep system are on the right throttle (electrical) and to the right of the right throttle (mechanical). See the :ref:`throttle` and the :ref:`throttlequadrant`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:464
msgid "The wing-sweep hat on the right throttle is normally set to **AUTO** enabling CADC control of the wings, this is the upper position. The down position sets the wing-sweep to the **BOMB** mode, 55° or aft."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:467
msgid "The **AFT** and **FWD** (forward) positions enable manual movement aft of the CADC scheduled position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:469
msgid "The emergency wing-sweep handle on the throttle quadrant is used to control the mechanical emergency mode, see emergency mode above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:473
msgid "The wing-sweep indicator to the right of the ACM panel is used to indicate the current wing-sweep positions. The pointer on the left side shows the CADC scheduled wing position. The left tape shows the manually commanded position and the right tape shows the actual wing position."
msgstr ""

