#: ../../source/general.rst:485
msgid "The relevant warning and advisory lights are located on the :ref:`VDI` and the pilot :ref:`CAindicator`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:487
msgid "The **WING SWEEP** warning light on the right side of the VDI illuminates when both wing-sweep electrical channels are inoperable or the emergency mode is in use. If it illuminates without the emergency mode being used that mode should then be used as the electrical system might not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:490
msgid "The **WING SWEEP** caution light on the pilot caution - advisory indicator illuminates when at least one electrical wing-sweep channel is inoperable."
