#: ../../source/general.rst:494
msgid "Wing-Sweep System Test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:496
msgid "The wing-sweep system can be tested on the ground in pre-flight without moving the wings using the :ref:`MTPanel`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:498
msgid "To conduct the test, set the wing-sweep mode to **AUTO** and push the **MASTER RESET** button. Set the **MASTER TEST** switch to **WG SWP**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:501
msgid "The CADC commanded position indicator on the wing-sweep indicator will now move to 44°. The **WING SWEEP** and **FLAP** light will illuminate on the pilot :ref:`CAindicator` and the **REDUCE SPEED** warning light on the :ref:`VDI`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:504
msgid "The **WING SWEEP** advisory light will illuminate after 3 seconds into test, turn off and then illuminate again at 8 seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:506
msgid "When the CADC commanded position indicator moves forward to the 20° position the test is over and the above light will turn off. The **MASTER TEST** switch can now be set to **OFF** and the test is complete. The test will take about 25 seconds to complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:509
msgid "The **RUDDER AUTH** and/or **MACH TRIM** lights might illuminate and the control stick might move. This can be ignored."
msgstr ""

