#: ../../source/general.rst:1242
msgid "Adjacent to this selector is a readout drum on the upper right edge of the TID (**5**). It's used to indicate the type of steering information currently displayed to the pilot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:1245
msgid "Possible steering type shown are: destination (DEST), data link command heading (D/L), azimuth lead collision steering (LD CLSN), collision steering (CLSN), lead pursuit steering (LD PURST), pursuit steering (PURST), TACAN radial (TACAN) and manually set commanded heading (MAN)."
