msgid "Stored Heading Alignment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3418
msgid "A feature of the INS that allows for quick-reaction response is the stored-heading alignment. The aircraft has to be parked and tied down in the alert position (wheel-chocks in DCS) for this procedure to be successful. Additionally the aircraft heading has to be stored with a reference alignment before the aircraft is being powered down (and back up again)."
